track_notes:
It is not the shortest but it is the nicest!
10km to walk (up and down) the last part (100 meters) you need to climb some easy rocks. Be careful if you have vertigo. In winter wait the is no snow and the stone are dry; in summer with hight temperature bring at least 2 liters of water.
track_title: Not the shortest way to summit

track_notes: By this track you can go on 2 summits not difficult for fitted OM. At the far end to reach the summit of Brec dUtelle you need your hands cos there are some easy rocks to climb. Go there only if no rain and in summer take a least 2 liters of water, the landscape is wonderfull
track_title: Easy way to a double 4 points summits
